		        <figcaption>The San Andreas fault in central California. A &quot;creeping&quot; section (green) separates locked stretches north of San Juan Bautista and south of Cholame. The Parkfield section (red) is a transition zone between the creeping and southern locked section. Stippled area marks the surface rupture in the 1857 Fort Tejon earthquake.</figcaption>
